==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Somebody who sells small items, either door-to-door, from a stall or in the street; a [[peddler]], a [[hawker]].
# Somebody who sells things in an aggressive or showy manner.
# Somebody who writes [[advertisement]]s for the radio or for TV.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|huckster||}}

# To sell or offer goods from place to place, to [[peddle]].
# To [[haggle]], to [[wrangle]], or to [[bargain]].
# To sell goods aggressively or in a showy manner.

